videos.description: Shaquille Morris finds Zach Brown who takes it to the rim for a sweet dunk early in the first half.
videos.headline: Wichita State's Brown cuts for dunk

videos.description: Mark Vital denies Darral Willis Jr.'s shot at the rim in the first half.
videos.headline: Baylor's Vital rises up for monster block

videos.description: Conner Frankamp drains back-to-back 3-pointers in the first half against Baylor.
videos.headline: Frankamp knocking in 3's for the Shockers

videos.description: Manu Lecomte gets through defenders and makes a nice one-handed basket for Baylor.
videos.headline: Lecomte hits nice lefty jumper

videos.description: Wichita State leads 33-29 at halftime, but head coach Gregg Marshall wants his team to make more stops against Baylor in the second half.
videos.headline: Marshall: 'We got to play tougher'

videos.description: Landry Shamet passes to Rashard Kelly who takes it from under the basket and dunks it in for the Shockers.
videos.headline: Shamet feeds Kelly for one-handed slam

videos.description: Landry Shamet feeds Shaquille Morris who slams it and gets the foul in the second half.
videos.headline: Wichita State's Morris smashes dunk for and -1

videos.description: King McClure takes on two defenders for the basket and foul.
videos.headline: Baylor's McClure makes tricky and-1 layup

videos.description: Zach Brown grabs the defensive rebound and Darral Willis Jr. dunks it in for the Shockers with under 5 minutes left in the game against Baylor.
videos.headline: Willis's throwdown widens Shockers' lead

videos.description: Although No.8 Wichita State defeated No. 16 Baylor 69-62, Shockers head coach Gregg Marshall says Baylor is a very good team and this is a significant win for Wichita State.
videos.headline: Marshall: 'Baylor will be in the NCAA tournament'
